Package ru.danilarassokhin.progressive.annotation

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Autofill
    Represents field or constructor which can be injected with some value from Dependency Injection container Not inherited value - specifies bean name for auto injection in field qualifiers - specifies bean names for auto injection as method parameters Autofill strategy In fields: if value (bean name) is specified, then searches for bean with given class and name.
    Components
    Point on specific class DI container must look at Not inherited
    ComponentScan
    Asks Dependency Injection container to scan packages for beans Not inherited value - array of package names to scan for @GameBean annotated classes
    FromParent
    Marks field in GameScript to be filled from some parent GameObject's GameScript Not inherited
    GameBean
    Marks class or method as bean provider for Dependency Injection container >Not inherited name - specifies bean name.
    IsGameScript
    Marks class as GameScript for GameObject
    Protected
    Just visual annotation for methods protected with GameSecurityManager Not securing methods!
    RequiredGameScript
    Defines required GameScripts for this GameScript Includes IsGameScript
    If lazy is true then only checks GameObject, which tries to add this GameScript, on having required scripts
    If lazy is false then creates required GameScripts and attaches them to GameObject if they hasn't been attached already Not inherited
